lag|American Samoa}}''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adcidl.com/Driving-in-American-Samoa.html |title=Driving in American Samoa |publisher=Adcidl.com |date= |accessdate=2015-02-20}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Australia}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|15&nbsp;years 9&nbsp;months ([[Australian Capital Territory|ACT]])\n16 (all other states and territories)\n| {{see also|Driving licence in Australia}}Learner drivers may drive under qualified supervision from the minimum age set in each state or territory.\n|-\n| {{flag|Fiji}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|17<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ltafiji.com/registration_licensing.php |title=Land Transport Authority - \"Steering Fiji Safely\" |publisher=Ltafiji.com |accessdate=2015-02-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141106015321/http://www.ltafiji.com/registration_licensing.php |archivedate=2014-11-06 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jasons.com/fiji/transportation-in-fiji |title=Transportation in Fiji - Jasons Fiji |publisher=Jasons.com |date= |accessdate=2015-02-20}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| ''{{flag|Guam}}''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ghsa.org/html/stateinfo/bystate/gu.html |title=Guam Highway Safety Laws |publisher=Ghsa.org |date= |accessdate=2015-02-20}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Marshall Islands}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iexplore.com/dmap/Marshall+Islands/Do's+and+Don'ts |title=Marshall Islands Travel Tips |accessdate=August 27, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070127010248/http://www.iexplore.com/dmap/Marshall%2BIslands/Do%27s%2Band%2BDon%27ts |archivedate=January 27, 2007 }}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|New Zealand}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16\n| {{see also|Driving licence in New Zealand}}The minimum age to obtain a car or motorcycle learner licence which allows driving under supervision is 16. The minimum possible age to obtain a full licence, without any supervision or conditions, is 17\u00bd years if a driver completes an advanced driving course.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nzta.govt.nz/licence/getting/cars/car-licence.html |title=Your car licence |publisher=Nzta.govt.nz |accessdate=20 February 2015}}</ref> Without an advanced driving course, the minimum age is 18, the same as a heavy vehicle licence.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.drivingtests.co.nz/resources/class-2-truck-licence/ |title=Class 2 licence |accessdate=1 September 2017}}</ref>\n|- \n| ''{{flag|Northern Mariana Islands}}''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|15&nbsp;years 6&nbsp;months<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ghsa.org/html/stateinfo/bystate/nmi.html |title=Northern Mariana Islands Highway Safety Laws |publisher=Ghsa.org |date= |accessdate=2015-02-20}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Papua New Guinea}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|18{{citation needed|date=December 2014}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Tonga}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iexplore.com/dmap/Tonga/Do's+and+Don'ts |title=Tonga \u2014 Travel Tips |publisher=iExplore |date= |accessdate=2015-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050307041704/http://www.iexplore.com/dmap/Tonga/Do's+and+Don'ts |archive-date=2005-03-07 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n{{Youth rights sidebar}}\n*[[Youth]]\n*[[Youth suffrage]]\n*[[Youth rights]]\n*[[Age of candidacy]]\n*[[Voting age]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Law country lists}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Countries By Minimum Driving Age}}\n[[Category:Law-related lists]]\n[[Category:Minimum ages]]\n[[Category:Traffic law]]\n[[Category:Lists of countries|Driving Age]]\n", "text_old": "The '''minimum driving age''' is the minimum age at which a person may obtain a [[driver's licence]] to lawfully drive a motor vehicle on public roads. That age is determined by and for each jurisdiction and is most commonly set at 18 years of age, but learner drivers may be permitted on the road at an earlier age under supervision. Before reaching the minimum age for a driver's licence or anytime afterwards, the person wanting the licence would normally be tested for driving ability and knowledge of road rules before being issued with a licence, provided he or she is above the minimum driving age. Countries with the lowest driving ages (17 and below) are Canada, El Salvador, Iceland, Israel, Malaysia, Australia, New Zealand, the Philippines, the United Kingdom (mainland), United States and Zimbabwe. In several jurisdictions in the United States and Canada, drivers can be as young as 14 (with parental supervision).\n\nMost jurisdictions recognise driver's licences issued by another jurisdiction, which may result in a young person who obtains a licence in a jurisdiction with a low minimum driving age being permitted to drive in a jurisdiction which normally has a higher driving age.\n\nThe minimum age may vary depending on vehicle type. This list refers to the minimum driving age for a light motor vehicle (typically under 3500 kg gross vehicle mass) or motorcycle, where noted.\n\n== Africa ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! width=\"100\" | State\n! width=\"130\" | Minimum driving age\n! width=\"300\" | Notes\n|-\n| {{flag|Algeria}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|18\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Cameroon}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16{{citation needed|date=August 2016|reason=Source}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Egypt}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aupairinamerica.com/resources/culture_quests/egypt.asp |title=Au Pairs from Egypt - Culture Quests |publisher=Aupairinamerica.com |date= |accessdate=2015-02-20}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Eswatini}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref name=\"google1\"/>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Ethiopia}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|18<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adcidl.com/Driving-in-Ethiopia.html |title=Driving in Ethiopia |publisher=Adcidl.com |date= |accessdate=2015-02-20}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Ghana}}\n| style=\"text-align:cen