sh Superliga|2009\u201310]]\n|7||0||?||?||\u2013||\u2013||\u2013||\u2013||7||0\n|-\n!Total\n!57!!0!!?!!?!!2!!0!!0!!0!!59!!0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Career total\n!462!!10!!34!!1!!35!!1!!2!!0!!533!!12\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Denmark's goal tally first.''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1 || 2 June 1996 || [[Copenhagen]], Denmark || {{fb|GHA}} || 1\u20130 || 1\u20130 || [[Friendly match]]\n|-\n| 2 || 28 June 1998 || [[Saint-Denis, Seine-Saint-Denis|Saint-Denis]], France || {{fb|NGA}} || 4\u20130 || 4\u20131 || [[1998 FIFA World Cup]]\n|}||\u2013\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n;OB\n*[[Danish Superliga|Danish 1st Division]]: [[1989 Danish 1st Division|1989]]\n*[[Danish Cup]]: [[1990\u201391 Danish Cup|1990\u201391]], [[1992\u201393 Danish Cup|1992\u201393]], [[2006\u201307 Danish Cup|2006\u201307]]\n\n;A.C. Milan\n*[[Serie A]]: [[1998\u201399 Serie A|1998\u201399]]\n*[[Coppa Italia]]: [[2002\u201303 Coppa Italia|2002\u201303]]\n*[[UEFA Champions League]]: [[2002\u201303 UEFA Champions League|2002\u201303]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[Danish Player of the Year|Danish ''Player of the Year'']]: 1994\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Literature==\n* {{cite book | first = J\u00f8rgen | last = Aagaard | title = Thomas Helveg \u2013 f\u00f8dt til at l\u00f8be |trans-title=Thomas Helveg \u2013 born to run | location = Denmark | year = 2001 | isbn = 87-7831-249-3 | language = Danish}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.dbu.dk/landshold/landsholdsdatabasen/PlayerInfo/985 Danish national team profile] {{in lang|da}}\n* [http://www.ex-canaries.co.uk/players/helveg.htm Career information at ex-canaries.co.uk]\n* {{SR/Olympics profile|he/thomas-helveg-1}}\n\n{{Danish Football Player of the Year}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title= Denmark squads\n|bg= #e11b22\n|fg= white\n|list1=\n{{Denmark football squad 1992 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Denmark squad UEFA Euro 1996}}\n{{Denmark squad 1998 FIFA World C